        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "ITS",
          "Next Exercise is Correct",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "912 students - Assistments Math 2004-2005\n\n3136 students - Assistments Math 2005-2006\n\n5046 students -  e Assistments\nMath 2006–2007\n\n",
          "3 Cohorts of Assistments Math",
          "ITS logs",
          "[D-KC, G-KC, M-KC, N-KC, P-KC]",
          "BKT is based on Hiden Markov Models, where the observations are the answers to previous questions (correct or incorrect).  This bi-partition is not always clear.",
          "The authors introduce a tripartite of representing each element of the BKT sequence:\n\nUnlearned State/Learning State/Learned State",
          "Students with fewer than 100 learning processes were excluded.\n\nEach learner is usually represented by the sequence of exercises within a knowledge component - a binary of learned state and unlearned state.\n\nAuthors simulate the bipartite vs the tripartite data representation using synthetic data - with results being clearly better for TPS.\n\nEach learner is ultimately represented by the sequences in each of the 5 considered knowledge components.",
          "Original BKT\nTLS-BKT",
          "10-fold Cross-Validation",
          "D-KC: {AUC: 0.8036 - TLS-BKT on 2004 data}\n\nG-KC: {AUC: 0.7653 - TLS-BKT on 2006 data}\n\nM-KC: {AUC: 0.7510 - TLS-BKT on 2006 data}\n\nN-KC: {AUC: 0.8394 - TLS-BKT on 2006 data}\n\nP-KC: {AUC: 0.8367 - TLS-BKT on 2004 data}\n\nAll-KC: {AUC: 0.8056 - TLS-BKT on 2004 data} ",
          "Before going into the real datasets, the authors test the performance of both traditional BKT and TLS-BKT on random subsets of the datasets.\n\nOne model is created for each individual knowledge component.\n\nHere, they consider multiple metrics beyond the AUC score: Distinction, Accuracy, RMSE and Standard Deviation.\n\nTLS-BKT outperforms BKT on every benchmark test.\n\nNeed to validate, but it seems that there is one model per knowledge component, which would make such a model very difficult to create in practice.",
          "Lacks generalization to environments outside Assistments Math.\n\nEvaluation on the full real data does not consider all metrics used for the randomly selected data data. \n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 10
    }
  ],
